Good morning. Google's hardware ambitions are on full display this week, confirming a trend that CIOs should welcome, but doing little to establish itself as a serious vendor to the business community.
In addition to a much anticipated new tablet computer and a new home entertainment device, Google put Google Glass on display Wednesday at its I/O Conference in San Francisco (more detailed news below).  employees work
out at the company gym, attend free movies at the company theater and enjoy

company paternalism will soon be put to the test by plans to cut $325
million in labor costs by the year 2000.
